{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_72","type":"agent_message","text":"The GraalVM metadata reference uses `**/…` globs even for resources at the classpath root. Our entries used bare filenames, which likely explains why the resources counted during image build still weren’t discoverable through `ClassLoader.getResources(\"reference.conf\")`. I’m switching the Akka resource globs to the documented form and rerunning the targeted test."}}
